VALUES ('180926c1-48aa-41c8-a653-296e0392c42c', 'Which choice most logically completes the text?', 'Economists observed that small retailers adapted faster than national chains when supply chains stalled, partly because they could reorder from local wholesalers within days. National chains waited for centralized distribution centers to reopen and could not pivot without corporate approval cycles. Corner shops that phoned alternate suppliers during the stall retained higher customer loyalty scores eighteen months later, while chains bound to uniform pricing algorithms could not shift product mix as quickly. Measurement protocols held unrelated variables stable across repeated observation cycles. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. Follow-up work will test whether the pattern holds across additional sites and populations.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It can be inferred that every national retail chain will permanently shrink its store footprint because the study proves large firms cannot survive any future.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Speculative Narrative] Speculative Narrative: It can be inferred that every national retail chain will permanently shr… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."},{"id":"B","text":"It can be inferred that customer loyalty and product mix flexibility are the same operational metric and therefore always increase together during supply stalls.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Equivocation Error] Equivocation: It can be inferred that customer loyalty and product mix flexibility are… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."},{"id":"C","text":"It can be inferred that supply-chain stalls must have been caused by national chains'' inability to reorder from local wholesalers within days. reflecting the bounded.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Reverse Conditional] Reverse Conditional: It can be inferred that supply-chain stalls must have been caused by nat… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."},{"id":"D","text":"It can be inferred that local supplier relationships helped small retailers adapt faster during supply-chain disruptions than organizational scale alone would predict.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Logically necessary from the stated premises; requires no speculative leap beyond the text."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Identify stated logic
