VALUES ('9042b84d-33dd-41f9-9159-62c534a16f6b', 'Which choice most logically follows from the passage as a whole?', 'Archaeologists discovered pottery shards containing residue of fermented grain at site layers associated with a ceremonial plaza rather than domestic kitchens. Chemical tests identified compounds consistent with controlled fermentation but not with large-scale storage for everyday consumption. Nearby hearths showed feasting debris concentrated on solstice dates. Residue profiles from adjacent domestic settlements lacked the same fermentation markers, suggesting the practice was localized to ritual contexts rather than routine meal preparation. Independent reviewers noted that alternative explanations have not yet been fully excluded in parallel cohorts. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It can be inferred that fermentation compounds and feasting debris are interchangeable evidence that always prove identical cultural practices across all ancient sites.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Speculative Narrative] Equivocation: It can be inferred that fermentation compounds and feasting debris are i… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."},{"id":"B","text":"It can be inferred that solstice feasting must have caused the fermentation compounds because feasting debris and fermentation markers never appear together otherwise.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Equivocation Error] Reverse Conditional: It can be inferred that solstice feasting must have caused the fermentat… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."},{"id":"C","text":"It can be inferred that the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than for daily meals according to the material evidence recovered.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (C). Logically necessary from the stated premises; requires no speculative leap beyond the text."},{"id":"D","text":"It can be inferred that modern craft breweries could authentically recreate every ancient recipe if archaeologists published complete chemical profiles from each shard.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Reverse Conditional] Equivocation: It can be inferred that modern craft breweries could authentically recre… cannot be proven solely from the premises given."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Step 1 — Identify stated logic
Focus on {{yellow:storage}} in the passage. The implication item asks you to identify stated logic before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Extend with reasonable limits
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On hard items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Confirm the implication
Choice C is correct: It can be inferred that the community brewed beverages for ritual gatherings rather than for daily meals according to the material evidence recovered..

Distractor analysis:
- A: [Speculative Narrative] Equivocation: It can be inferred that fermentation compounds and feasting debris are i… cannot be proven solely from the premises given.
- B: [Equivocation Error] Reverse Conditional: It can be inferred that solstice feasting must have caused the fermentat… cannot be proven solely from the premises given.
- D: [Reverse Conditional] Equivocation: It can be inferred that modern craft breweries could authentically recre… cannot be proven solely from the premises given.', NULL, 'Information and Ideas', 'Inferences', 'reading_writing', 'information', 'INF', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"rw_subtype":"implication","dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_format":"passage_mc","explanation_v2":true,"generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","master_manual_section":7,"regen_phase2":true,"regen_at":"2026-06-13T22:21:16.961Z","regen_seed_offset":100000}'::jsonb, now(), now());
